@Node "Terms" "RxCD Terms"

  @{b}Terms@{ub}@{uu}


    The main terms used in this guide are:

    - @{b}ID@{ub}
      The device descriptor as returned by @{"CDCreate()" LINK "CDCreate"}
      it is an integral number

    - @{b}CD@{ub}
      An AmigaDOS device name (f.e. "CD0") or an ID

    - @{b}CDName@{ub}
      An AmigaDOS device name (f.e. "atapi.device")

    - @{b}Track@{ub}
      A sub-division of the CD-ROM media. A disc has from 1 to 99
      tracks. The data within a track are always of the same
      type: DATA or AUDIO. A disc can start at any track number.
      Before an audio track there me a so called pause area.
      Before a data track there may be a so called pre gap area.
      After a data track there may be a so called post gap area.

    - @{b}Index@{ub}
      An index is a subdivision of a CD-ROM track. A track can
      have from 1 to 99 index numbers. Index numbers within a
      track are sequential starting with 1. In the pause area the
      index is 0.

    - @{b}Address@{ub}
      Physical address of a frame on a CD

    - @{b}Frame@{ub}
      1/75 of a second. A physical sector on CD-ROM media. Also
      the F field unit of a MSF CD-ROM address

    - @{b}MSF@{ub}
      Minutes/Seconds/Frames rappresents an address on a CD
      addr =manipulate*75*60 + S*75 + F it is also used to
      indicate a duration (of a track, a set of tracks or the
      whole CDROM).

    - @{b}stem or stemName@{ub}
      A valid ARexx variable name e.g. var var.0 var.name

    - @{b}Types of arguments:@{ub}
      . D    Any data    --    --
      . N    Numeric     /N    ARexx integral number
      . S    Symbol      /S    ARexx valid symbol
      . V    StemName    /V    As S but with length<32
      . O    StemName    /O    As V but maybe "" also

@EndNode

